        which was investigated on the date of: &lt;date&gt;. </font>
    </p>
    <p style="font-weight: normal"><font face="Courier New, monospace">The
        SOC has added information within the ticket detailing behavior
        that
        has not been seen consistently throughout the network and may
        require
        additional analysis, escalation or resources to understand. </font>
    </p>
    <p style="font-weight: normal"><font face="Courier New, monospace">Currently
        the system referenced in the ticket is consistently sending ICMP
        traffic to an IP address within the ticket that is not owned,
        operated or part of &lt;organization&gt;. The traffic noted is
        60%
        higher than all other systems in the last 90 – 100 day period
        and
        is 150x more prevalent since &lt;first seen date&gt; which was
        &lt;number of days ago&gt;</font></p>
    <p style="font-weight: normal"><font face="Courier New, monospace">SOC
        team is currently requesting the following for management
        approval: </font>
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p style="font-weight: normal"><font
            face="Courier New, monospace">Wireshark capture from the
            network level where &lt;system&gt; is located. </font> </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p style="font-weight: normal"><font
            face="Courier New, monospace">Wireshark capture from
            &lt;endpont name&gt; system that has been affected. </font>
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p style="font-weight: normal"><font face="Courier New, monospace">We’d
        like to understand what, or why these packets are communicating
        to
        make a stronger determination into the root cause of these
        packets
        being sent/received. </font>
    </p>
    <p style="font-weight: normal"><font face="Courier New, monospace">At
        this time, additional investigations have been halted as to not
        impact the integrity of the potential of network artifact
        collection
        (direct access may stop the current communication and we are
        trying
        to avoid this). Once we have approval to do so, we are
        requesting an
        additional two days of analysis for the packet captures but will
        continue additional investigatory actions once we have obtained
        the
        captures. </font>
    </p>
